  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "paragraph_name": "ERROR-LOG-RECORD",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines the layout of an error log record. It contains fields for capturing the date and time of the error (ERR-DATE, ERR-TIME), the application and program where the error occurred (ERR-APPLICATION, ERR-PROGRAM), the location within the program (ERR-LOCATION), the severity level of the error (ERR-LEVEL), and the subsystem involved (ERR-SUBSYSTEM). It also includes fields for specific error codes (ERR-CODE-1, ERR-CODE-2), a descriptive error message (ERR-MESSAGE), and an event key for tracking purposes (ERR-EVENT-KEY). The ERR-LEVEL and ERR-SUBSYSTEM fields use 88-level condition names to define specific values for error levels (ERR-LOG, ERR-INFO, ERR-WARNING, ERR-CRITICAL) and subsystems (ERR-APP, ERR-CICS, ERR-IMS, ERR-DB2, ERR-MQ, ERR-FILE). This structure is intended to be used for creating and writing error records to an error log file or database.",
